-- Eurostar Cancels Almost Half of Its Trains on Weather
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2010-12-02T09:20:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-01/eurostar-cancels-almost-half-of-high-speed-trains-as-weather-snarls-europe.html
(Corrects story that ran late yesterday to show that
services are between London and Paris, London and Brussels.)  Eurostar Group Ltd., which runs the
high-speed trains between London and Paris or Brussels,
cancelled seven of its services between London and Paris
tomorrow and five between London and Brussels because of weather
conditions, spokesperson Lesley Retallack said by phone.  The company normally operates up to 18 daily services
between London and Paris and up to 10 between London and
Brussels, Retallack said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Jack Jordan  in London at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 